<section id="aboutRight">
    <h2>About the Editor</h2>
    <p class="lead">“Renata Bushko is a leading visionary concerning the applications of information technology in health care and health promotion. Her prodigious organizational skills, coupled with her revealing intellectual insights and tremendous drive have spurred major advancements in digital health. For example, Renata accurately predicted 20 years ago the current explosion of health sensors, smartphones wellness apps, nano-robots, and connected m-health and e-health. Her eye-opening 2002, 2005 and 2009 future of heath technology books and 20 Future of Health Technology summits paved the way to the worldwide health information technology revolution bringing together more than 1000 health and technology leaders. She is a strategic thinker and compassionate leader and I heartily endorse her.“
<br><cite>Gary L. Kreps, Ph.D., FAAHB University Distinguished Professor George Mason University</cite></p>
    <h3>Renata Bushko's Bio</h3>
    <hr>
<p>“Renata Bushko’s Strategy for the Future of Health book is just like Renata brilliant, bold and brave and has exponential power to pull you into the future." Ray Kurzweil, Inventor, Author and Futurist</p>
<p>“If you understand something in only one way, then you don’t understand it at all. So take this journey with Renata to envision many versions of future health technology.” Professor Marvin Minsky, MIT</p>
<p>Renata G. Bushko, M.S. is Author, Futurist and Founder of the Future of Health Technology Institute (FHTI), a health technology think-tank and Strategy Advisory dedicated to defining the health technology development and investment strategy for the 21st century. She founded Future of Health Technology Institute in 1996 and has since chaired twenty Future of Health Technology Summits and worked with more than 1000 world-class experts. These summits engage leading minds from the technology and health fields in envisioning the future of technology for global healthcare. She authored and edited three visionary books: Future of Health Technology, Future of Intelligent and Extelligent Health Environment, and Strategy for the Future of Health. Her new book World Health Strategy will be e-published in 2016 for the 20th Anniversary of FHTI and in honor of Marvin Minsky.</p>
<p>Renata is also producer of Future of Health Technology video educational channel featuring inventors, scientists, and investors leading health-tech revolution <a href="http://www.youtube.com/user/FutureofHealthTech" role="link" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/user/FutureofHealthTech</a>. She is often invited by both government agencies and private sector to design and lead innovation sessions aimed at generating breakthrough ideas and strategic plans for the future.</p>
<p>She was invited to represent US at WHO’S First Medical Devices Forum and Prince Mahidol Conference in Bangkok, High Level eHealth European ministerial meeting and to design Future of Health programs for CDC and Rockefeller Foundation. Previously she served on national healthcare programs organized by Vice President Albert Gore, Dr. C. Everett Koop, and former secretary of Health and Human Services, Dr. L. Sullivan. She was an advisor on health technology investment issues in the US, UK, Puerto Rico, Australia, New Zealand, and Poland while representing US health standards organizations to Australia and Asia.</p>
<p>  She worked for 15 years as an executive in computer industry and as an analyst for IDC defining future trends in technology. She holds a Master of Science degree in Electrical Engineering and Computer Science with specialization in intelligent systems from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT) and a BA in Computer Science and Economics from Smith College. Her graduate work at MIT was done under Professor Marvin Minsky — one of the founders of the field of Artificial Intelligence.</p>
